OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,412,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1781722095
OL,3,C'Mistakes made' in Donohoe
OL,4,Cinvestigation but not deliberately,
OL,5,Cdetective says
OL,7,FEarlier in her examination, Ms
OL,8,FCampbell contested that Mr Phillips
OL,9,F"pursued a hypothesis that blamed a
OL,10,Fchild, that he did this by choice".
OL,12,F"I disagree with the phrase I blamed
OL,13,Fhim," he said.
OL,15,FMs Campbell then clarified that he
OL,16,F"pursued a hypothesis that Noah did
OL,17,Fthis by choice".
OL,19,FHe replied: "Yes, that is where I felt
OL,20,Fthe evidence and information took us."
OL,26,@qD@AOUrD@bO]tD@AOUuD@EO]xD@AOUyD@OO]{D@
OL,26,AMOU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/16
